Rising Oil Prices ‘May Harm China’s Monetary Policy,’ WSJ Says

-- B y   C h r i s   P e t e r s o n
-- 
2011-03-30T03:57:41Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-30/rising-oil-prices-may-harm-china-s-monetary-policy-wsj-says.html
Rising oil prices may interfere
with  China ’s carefully crafted  monetary policy , making it harder
to manage the country’s real estate bubble, the Wall Street
Journal reported, citing an interview with Hans Timmer, director
of the World Bank’s Development Prospects Group.  Rising commodity prices could trigger a spiraling increase
in inflation, something which China’s government is very
concerned about, Timmer told the WSJ.     To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Chris Peterson  at 
 cpeterson@bloomberg.net  